<h1>What are the <em>Student Voice</em> Surveys?</h1>
<p>Every semester the SRC sends out an email to all enrolled students inviting them to join the <em> Student Voice</em>. Over 3,000 students agree to take the surveys, and each survey receives between 1,300 to 2,500 responses. Since the <em>Student Voice</em> group represents a broad statistical cross-section of campus, the Student Representative Council can generally conclude that the results of the surveys represent the overall opinion of the BYU-Idaho student body on a particular issue.</p>
<h1>How Do I Join?</h1>
<p>The SRC sends an email to all students enrolled in at least one class at the beginning of each semester. Click the link in that email and respond "yes" to begin receiving the <em>Student Voice</em> surveys.</p>
<p>We are currently working on a way for "Off-Track" students to receive the <em>Student Voice</em> surveys. Check back here for updates.</p>
